<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> Ewen and Ewen, <i><a href="/w/index.php?title=Typecasting:_On_the_Arts_and_Sciences_of_Human_Inequality&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Typecasting: On the Arts and Sciences of Human Inequality (page does not exist)">Typecasting: On the Arts and Sciences of Human Inequality</a></i>, 2006, 3-10.</li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> &lt;<a href="http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0877791325&amp;id=2yJusP0vrdgC&amp;pg=PA250&amp;lpg=PA250&amp;ots=nXvVkdB_U4&amp;dq=cliche+origin&amp;sig=f5UQIqottU546aRBe3zlm-9Q7kM#PPA250,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0877791325&amp;id=2yJusP0vrdgC&amp;pg=PA250&amp;lpg=PA250&amp;ots=nXvVkdB_U4&amp;dq=cliche+origin&amp;sig=f5UQIqottU546aRBe3zlm-9Q7kM#PPA250,M1" rel="nofollow">Merriam-Webster's Dictionary of English Usage.</a>&gt; Springfield, Illinois: Merriam-Webster, Inc., 1994. p. 250.</li>
